      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YUKANUMA (2) got the prize two runs ago at this track. Couldn't quite follow that up last time out when chased down for third over 2150m at Ipswich. Gets in light with the 3kg claimer engaged and should prove tough to hold out. RING AHOY (1) registered a strong win at Wyong two runs ago and then got home strongly last start at Inverell after settling a long way off them. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. BONFIDELITY (3) also comes through Inverell, where she stuck on soundly into fifth. That followed a win at Coffs Harbour at the previous outing. Will appreciate stepping back out to this sort of trip and finds a suitable race to return to the winner's circle. ROCK THE MACHINE (5) showed good early dash and raced on the speed last start before fading into sixth over 2200m at Coffs Harbour. Form prior stacks right up, so worth another chance.",
